# Eliminate redundant `getProject` round-trips in project-search resolution

## Problem

`resolveProjectBySlug()` and `resolveOrgProjectTarget()` both call `findProjectsBySlug()` which internally calls `getProject()` per org — fetching the **full** `SentryProject` object. But both functions **discard** that data and return only `{ org: string, project: string }`. Callers that need the project ID or full project details call `getProject()` a second time.

This is the same class of redundancy that PR #473 fixed for the issue short-ID path.

## Redundant callers (3 confirmed, each saves ~500-800ms)

| Command | File | What happens |
|---------|------|-------------|
| `dashboard create` | `src/commands/dashboard/create.ts:97-106` | `resolveProjectBySlug()` → `fetchProjectId()` re-calls `getProject` just to get `.id` |
| `project delete` | `src/commands/project/delete.ts:244-248` | `resolveOrgProjectTarget()` → `getProject()` re-fetches for display name |
| `project view` | `src/commands/project/view.ts:103-104` | `resolveProjectBySlug()` → `fetchProjectDetails()` → `getProject()` re-fetches |

## Non-redundant callers (no changes needed)

These use only `{ org, project }` slugs for scoping, then call a **different** API:
- `event/view.ts`, `log/view.ts`, `init.ts`, `trace/list.ts`, `span/list.ts`, `log/list.ts`

## Root cause

```
resolveProjectBySlug(slug)
  → findProjectsBySlug(slug)
      → listOrganizations() + N × getProject(org, slug)  ← fetches FULL SentryProject
  → return { org: foundProject.orgSlug, project: foundProject.slug }  ← DISCARDS project data
```

## Approach: Widen return types to carry project data through

### Step 1: Extend `resolveProjectBySlug()` return type

**File: `src/lib/resolve-target.ts` (lines 954-1010)**

Current signature returns `Promise<{ org: string; project: string }>`.

Change to return the full project too:
```typescript
export type ResolvedProjectBySlug = {
  org: string;
  project: string;
  /** Full project data already fetched by findProjectsBySlug — avoids re-fetch */
  projectData: SentryProject;
};
```

At line 1006, change `return { org, project }` to `return { org, project, projectData: foundProject }`.

Existing callers that destructure `{ org, project }` continue to work unchanged.

### Step 2: Extend `resolveOrgProjectTarget()` return type

**File: `src/lib/resolve-target.ts` (lines 1094-1170)**

Add optional `projectData` to `ResolvedOrgProject`:
```typescript
export type ResolvedOrgProject = {
  org: string;
  project: string;
  /** Available when resolved via project-search (avoids re-fetch) */
  projectData?: SentryProject;
};
```

In the `project-search` case (line 1150), change to:
```typescript
return { org: match.orgSlug, project: match.slug, projectData: match };
```

Other cases (`explicit`, `auto-detect`) continue returning just `{ org, project }`.

### Step 3: Fix `dashboard/create.ts` — use `projectData.id`

**File: `src/commands/dashboard/create.ts` (lines 97-106)**

```diff
 case "project-search": {
   const found = await resolveProjectBySlug(...);
-  const pid = await fetchProjectId(found.org, found.project);
+  const pid = toNumericId(found.projectData.id);
   return {
     orgSlug: found.org,
     projectIds: pid !== undefined ? [pid] : [],
   };
 }
```

Eliminates 1 HTTP round-trip.

### Step 4: Fix `project/delete.ts` — use `projectData` when available

**File: `src/commands/project/delete.ts` (lines 244-248)**

```diff
 const { org: orgSlug, project: projectSlug } =
   await resolveOrgProjectTarget(parsed, cwd, COMMAND_NAME);
-const project = await getProject(orgSlug, projectSlug);
+// project-search already fetched the project; explicit/auto-detect paths need a fetch
+const resolved = await resolveOrgProjectTarget(parsed, cwd, COMMAND_NAME);
+const project = resolved.projectData ?? await getProject(resolved.org, resolved.project);
```

Eliminates 1 HTTP round-trip in the project-search path. Explicit path still fetches (needed for validation).

### Step 5: Fix `project/view.ts` — skip re-fetch when data available

**File: `src/commands/project/view.ts` (lines 98-110, 228-240)**

In the `project-search` resolution case, pass `projectData` through to `ResolvedTarget`. Then in `fetchProjectDetails()`:

```diff
 async function fetchProjectDetails(target: ResolvedTarget): Promise<ProjectWithDsn | null> {
   const result = await withAuthGuard(async () => {
     const [project, dsn] = await Promise.all([
-      getProject(target.org, target.project),
+      target.projectData
+        ? Promise.resolve(target.projectData)
+        : getProject(target.org, target.project),
       tryGetPrimaryDsn(target.org, target.project),
     ]);
     return { project, dsn };
   });
```

Requires adding `projectData?: SentryProject` to the `ResolvedTarget` type in the relevant type definition.

Eliminates 1 HTTP round-trip in the project-search path. Other paths still fetch normally.

